  <!-- Article Main Layout-->
  <section class="article-layout">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="article-layout__wrapper">
        <!-- Article Content -->
        <article class="article-content js-article-content">
          <p>
            The opening day of finals at the ISSF competition in
            <strong>Granada, Spain</strong> brought excitement across all 10m
            individual events, but it was Azerbaijan's
            <strong>Ruslan Lunev</strong> who delivered the standout performance
            of the day. Lunev claimed
            <strong>gold in the 10m Air Pistol Men</strong> event, showcasing a
            confident and composed display on the international stage.
          </p>

          <img
            src="assets/images/news/ruslan-lunev-gold-10m-air-pistol-issf-granada/content-img-01.jpg"
            alt="Athlete Ruslan Lunev"
            width="840"
            height="480"
          />

          <p>
            A winner and medalist of the ISSF Grand Prix, Lunev once again
            proved his class in a tense final. He held off strong competition,
            including Tokyo 2020 Olympic silver medalist
            <strong>Damir Mikec</strong> of Serbia, who finished second. Bronze
            went to South Korea's <strong>Wonho Lee</strong>, marking an
            impressive debut at ISSF level.
          </p>

          <p class="news-article-highlight">
            Despite strong performances across all events, the highlight of the
            day remained <strong>Ruslan Lunev's</strong> victory — a significant
            achievement for Azerbaijan on the international stage.
          </p>

          <blockquote>
            “This result reflects the dedication of our athletes and coaching
            staff. We are proud to represent Azerbaijan at the highest level.”
          </blockquote>

          <p>
            Coaches also highlighted the importance of long-term athlete
            development, emphasizing the federation’s investment in youth
            programs and international preparation camps.
          </p>
        </article>

